<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,726,823]" pageId="23" pageNumber="459">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1898" box="[278,474,726,751]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Pseudoanthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[278,474,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="459">Pseudoanthidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is represented by one subgenus, 
<emphasis box="[857,1124,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="459">
<taxonomicName authority="Belavadi, 2017" authorityName="Belavadi" authorityYear="2017" box="[857,1053,726,751]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Pseudoanthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto" status="s. str.">Pseudoanthidium</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1062,1124,727,750]" pageId="23" pageNumber="459" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Friese: female preoccipital carina behind gena rounded; propodeum not punctate; clypeal apex largely hidden by hair, without shining premarginal ridge; male S3 with comb of long, wavy bristles and S5 with comb at apex of apico-lateral projection.
</paragraph>
